## Proposal

### Please re-state the problem that we are trying to solve in this issue.
Emoji Picker Doesn't Close on User B's Side When User A Deletes a Message
### What is the root cause of that problem?
We have the logic here to hide the emoji picker when the `ReportActionItem` is unmounted. But when we delete a message that contains a child thread message this `ReportActionItem` isn't unmounted so the the emoji picker doesn't hide.

https://github.com/Expensify/App/blob/b30b55574bd3453c7c8d012aa39d62fe9de569f6/src/pages/home/report/ReportActionItem.js#L183
### What changes do you think we should make in order to solve the problem?
We should check if the action is deleted and has child thread message, we should hide the emoji picker

```
const isDeletedParentAction = ReportActionsUtils.isDeletedParentAction(props.action);
  const prevIsDeletedParentAction = usePrevious(props.action);

  useEffect(() => {
      if (isDeletedParentAction == prevIsDeletedParentAction) {
          return;
      }
      if (isDeletedParentAction && EmojiPickerAction.isActive(props.action.reportActionID)) {
          EmojiPickerAction.hideEmojiPicker(true);
      }
  }, [isDeletedParentAction, prevIsDeletedParentAction])
```

